what_to_do: Wake up! Snooze once, then reluctantly get out of bed. Check Instagram for a few minutes – gotta see what everyone's up to! Then a quick stretch and a mental pep talk to tackle the day. Yesterday I planned to try a new breakfast place, so I'm excited to see if I can make it.
Get ready! Quick shower, throw on a comfy outfit (probably something with a cute print).  I'm thinking about trying to learn a new braiding style for my hair – maybe I'll find a tutorial later.

Breakfast adventure! Head to 'Morning Dew Cafe' – I saw it on a local foodie blog. Hopefully, they have some unique pastries! I'm thinking about their lavender honey latte.  I'm also going to try to take some aesthetically pleasing photos for my foodstagram.
Walk to campus.  I'm going to try to memorize a new route – maybe I'll discover a hidden gem! I'm daydreaming about building a little app that helps people find secret spots in the city.

Algorithms class. Ugh, this is always a brain workout. I need to focus and take detailed notes. I'm hoping Professor Chen will explain the dynamic programming concepts a little clearer today. I'm also going to try to ask a clarifying question – even if it feels silly.

Lunch with Mei-Ling and Kevin. We're going to the student union – probably just grab some noodles. I want to ask Mei-Ling about her photography project – she's so talented! I also need to remind Kevin about our group project deadline next week.

Data Structures lab.  We're working on implementing a binary search tree today. I'm going to pair up with David – he's really good at debugging. I'm also going to try to find a short online tutorial on tree traversal algorithms for later.

Quick coffee break. I'm feeling a little drained. I'm going to try a new flavor at the campus coffee shop – maybe a matcha latte with a little something extra. I'm also going to browse Reddit for a few minutes – gotta see what's trending.

Online Python tutorial. I'm going to dedicate some time to brushing up on my Python skills. I found a course on Udemy about building web scrapers – that sounds really interesting! I'm also going to try to implement a simple script to download images from a specific website.

Dinner. I'm craving dumplings! I'm going to try that new dumpling place near the library. I'm hoping they have a spicy option. I'm also going to listen to a podcast while I eat – maybe something about tech or design.

Group project meeting with Kevin and Amy. We need to finalize the presentation slides. I'm a little nervous about presenting, but I'm going to try to be confident! I'm also going to suggest we practice our delivery a few times.

Relaxation time. Face mask, some chill music, and maybe a little bit of sketching. I'm thinking about designing a cute sticker for my laptop. I also want to look up some braiding tutorials – I really want to learn a fishtail braid!
Plan tomorrow. Check my calendar, make a to-do list. I need to remember to buy groceries and schedule a dentist appointment. I'm also going to jot down some ideas for my personal coding project.
Wind down and sleep. Read a few pages of a book. Hopefully, I'm not too wired from all the caffeine!
